Sentencas: A novel composite material based on mixture of samarium-doped ceria (SDC)-carbonate was studied as electrolyte in low temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase and microstructures of composite electrolyte were examined by XRD and SEM.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity was investigated by AC impedance spectroscopy at 400-700 degrees C in different atmospheres.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An abrupt change in the conductivity at about 500 degrees C indicates that different mechanisms affect transfer in different temperature ranges.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivity increases with the carbonate fraction above 500 degrees C.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivity in reduce atmosphere is higher than that in oxide atmosphere.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An anode-supported fuel cell using SDC-carbonate as electrolyte was fabricated and tested.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The result shows that all the composite electrolytes exhibit better performance than pure SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrolyte with 20wt% carbonate can achieve the highest power density of 415mW center dot cm(-2) and an open circuit voltage of 1.00V at 500 degrees C.
Titulo: A novel composite electrolyte based on CeO2 for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells
